The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Indian cricketers in search of roots
                                                                                                                       7                                      Indian cricketers in search of roots
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: Its a kind of a homecoming for a bunch of young cricketers from South Africa. And their objective of touring their mother country is to get a feel of the passion that the country has for cricket.         
	The Lenasia Cavaliers, a cricket club from the Guateng province of South Africa, are currently touring India  Calcutta to be precise.         
	The contingent consists of 16 cricketers have their roots in India. Coached by Hoosain Ayob, the team had arrived on December 25 and will be in the city till January 12.         
	We wanted the youngsters to feel how the game is treated in this country. And, for that we felt that theres no better place than Calcutta, said Ayob, who revealed that he first came to the city as an official of the South African team on its historic tour of India.         
	 Its basically more of an educational tour We hope the experience comes handy in the youngsters pursuit of a place in the South African team, added Ayob.         
	However, the coach, who was also a part of the International Cricket Councils cricket development programme in the African continent, rued that they missed the India-Sri Lanka one-day International (ODI) at the Eden on December 24 by a day.         
	Manager Azhar Saloojee informed that Cricket South Africa had bore a part of the expenses for the tour.         
	Before signing off, Ayob added: Lenasias association with cricket goes back a long way. For the record, current ICC chief executive officer, Haroon Lorgat, had played cricket for Lenasia for a long time.                                                                                                                     
